{
  "stem": "10478.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My, my, my parents, we all were members of the Reformed Church, a small church in Maastricht.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They practiced their religion by going twice to church on Sunday and by-- at home, you know, educating us, us in the Bible, Old and New Testament, and reading the Bible, and praying on the table, yeah.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we, we read quite a bit out of the Old and New Testament, yes--",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--on the-- on the table, when we have our sitting together.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Most, most, most was read by  my parents, yes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the moral lesson we got from the readings, and also from the teaching of our parents, was to [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] look after the poor, look after the people who are homeless, and so on.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were an example to that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we, we followed that  later on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That started very early in  my life, yes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was not before the war because there was practically no racism.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, we didn't knew-- didn't even know who was a Jew or not.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But after the-- 1932, when we had an influx of Jewish immigrants from Germany, then we became aware at what racism was and what hate was.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the only data we, we got was to listen to radio  and the papers what happens in Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was an eye-opener for us, what racism really was.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The persecution of the Jews, the way that they had to flee-- leave the country, and came to, to Holland and other countries, maybe.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and there was quite an influx, yeah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not at all.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we-- our city hall set up a committee when I was 19 years of age to look after those people.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
